cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on peer-to-peer content distribution systems over the Internet. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper specifically discusses the dissemination of video streams. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also possible categories as the paper discusses the parallelism and optimal piece sizes for distributing content. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the design trade-off in BitTorrent's choice of dividing pieces into subpieces.
